-- China Gun Crimes Fall 33.1% in First Five Months, Security Ministry Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-29T00:20:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/china-gun-crimes-fall-33-1-in-first-five-months-security-ministry-says.html

          
          
             The number of gun crimes in China
during the first five months fell 33.1 percent from a year
earlier, the Ministry of Public Security said on its website
yesterday. The number of crimes involving explosions declined by
13.4 percent, according to the ministry.  
          
          


  


        